-- 25-oracle-chain-builder.cell (R17, v0.2)
-- Tests: recursive oracle decomposition, ‚ä¢‚ä¢ spawner for sub-oracle refiners,
--        soft‚Üíhard classification, ‚ä¢‚àò refinement loop until convergence,
--        ‚ä¢= crystallized leaf checks, hierarchy assembly, wildcard deps
--
-- v0.2 changes from R16:
--   - File-scope ‚ä®? recovery policy (v0.2 blesses file-scope ‚ä®?)
--   - Wildcard deps (refiner-*‚Üífield, check-*‚Üífield) now v0.2-compliant:
--     resolves to ordered array by spawn order, ready when ALL matching frozen
--   - ‚ä¢‚ä¢ spawners: explicit accumulate mode for spawn-sub-decomposers
--     (refiners accumulate across ‚ä¢‚àò iterations); replace mode for
--     spawn-crystallizers (leaf checks rebuilt each time hierarchy changes)
--   - Oracles on decompose are aspirational under ‚ä¢‚àò management ‚Äî feedback
--     signals for the refinement loop, not hard gates
--   - Guard clause on assemble-hierarchy ensures all leaf checks are frozen
--   - ‚ä¢= expression language validated: verify-coverage uses only v0.2
--     primitives (len, and, if/then/else, comparisons)
--   - ‚ä¢‚àò label is "refine-loop" (v0.2: arbitrary label, not function name)
--   - ‚ä¢‚àò parameter bindings pass api-artifact fields as stable context
--   - v0.2 observation ‚ä¢= cells in trace for spec-level findings
--
-- Starts with soft oracle: "the API design is good."
-- Decomposes into specific sub-oracles. Recurses until all leaves
-- are deterministically checkable (‚ä¢=). Outputs an oracle hierarchy
-- from vague root to precise, crystallized leaves.

‚ä®? on failure:
  retry with ¬´oracle.failures¬ª appended to prompt
  max 2 attempts

‚ä®? on exhaustion:
  partial-accept(best)

‚ä¢ api-artifact
  given endpoints ‚â° "GET /users/{id} ‚Üí User, POST /users ‚Üí User, PUT /users/{id} ‚Üí User, DELETE /users/{id} ‚Üí 204, GET /users?page=N&limit=M ‚Üí User[], POST /users/{id}/roles ‚Üí Role"
  given naming ‚â° "kebab-case paths, camelCase JSON fields, plural resource nouns"
  given errors ‚â° "400 {error, message, details[]}, 401 Unauthorized, 403 Forbidden, 404 Not Found, 409 Conflict, 422 Unprocessable Entity, 500 Internal Server Error"
  given auth ‚â° "Bearer JWT in Authorization header, POST /auth/refresh, scopes: read:users write:users admin:users"
  yield endpoints, naming, errors, auth

  ‚ä® endpoints lists HTTP methods with paths and return types
  ‚ä® naming specifies conventions for paths, fields, and resources
  ‚ä® errors specifies status codes with response structures
  ‚ä® auth specifies the authentication scheme and scopes

‚ä¢ root-oracle
  given text ‚â° "the API design is good"
  given level ‚â° 0
  yield text, level

‚ä¢ decompose
  given root-oracle‚Üítext
  given api-artifact‚Üíendpoints
  given api-artifact‚Üínaming
  given api-artifact‚Üíerrors
  given api-artifact‚Üíauth
  yield sub-oracles[], classifications[], soft-count

  ‚à¥ Decompose the vague oracle ¬´root-oracle‚Üítext¬ª into 4-6 specific
    sub-oracles by examining the API artifact across these dimensions:

    - Endpoint design (REST conventions, resource modeling)
    - Naming consistency (paths, fields, resources)
    - Error handling (coverage, structure, semantics)
    - Authentication & authorization (scheme, scopes, flows)

    For each sub-oracle, classify it as:
    - "soft" ‚Äî still vague, needs further decomposition
      (e.g., "endpoints follow REST conventions")
    - "structural" ‚Äî checkable by pattern matching
      (e.g., "all paths use kebab-case")
    - "deterministic" ‚Äî checkable by exact value match
      (e.g., "error 400 response includes details[]")

    Output sub-oracles[] as oracle text strings, classifications[]
    aligned by index, and soft-count = number of "soft" entries.

  -- v0.2: These oracles are aspirational under ‚ä¢‚àò management.
  -- They serve as feedback signals for the refinement loop, not hard gates.
  ‚ä® len(sub-oracles) ‚â• 4
  ‚ä® len(sub-oracles) ‚â§ 6
  ‚ä® len(classifications) = len(sub-oracles)
  ‚ä® each classification ‚àà {"soft", "structural", "deterministic"}
  ‚ä® soft-count = count(classifications, c -> c = "soft")

‚ä¢‚ä¢ spawn-sub-decomposers
  given decompose‚Üísub-oracles
  given decompose‚Üíclassifications
  given api-artifact‚Üíendpoints
  given api-artifact‚Üínaming
  given api-artifact‚Üíerrors
  given api-artifact‚Üíauth
  given ¬ßrefiner-template
  yield ¬ßrefiner-cells[]
  until len(refiner-cells) = decompose‚Üísoft-count
  max 6
  accumulate

  ‚à¥ For each sub-oracle in ¬´decompose‚Üísub-oracles¬ª where the
    corresponding classification is "soft", spawn a refiner cell
    from ¬´¬ßrefiner-template¬ª. Each spawned cell receives the
    sub-oracle text and the full API artifact as context.

    Do NOT spawn refiners for sub-oracles already classified as
    "structural" or "deterministic" ‚Äî those are already leaves.

  ‚ä® len(refiner-cells) = decompose‚Üísoft-count
  ‚ä® each refiner targets exactly one soft sub-oracle

‚ä¢ refiner-template
  given oracle-text
  given endpoints
  given naming
  given errors
  given auth
  yield refined-oracles[], refined-classes[]

  ‚à¥ Decompose ¬´oracle-text¬ª into 2-4 more specific sub-oracles.
    Each should be closer to deterministically checkable.
    Classify each as "soft", "structural", or "deterministic".
    Prefer "deterministic" and "structural" ‚Äî only mark as "soft"
    if the assertion truly cannot be made more specific.

    Use the artifact fields ¬´endpoints¬ª, ¬´naming¬ª, ¬´errors¬ª, ¬´auth¬ª
    to ground each sub-oracle in a concrete, checkable property.

  ‚ä® len(refined-oracles) ‚â• 2
  ‚ä® len(refined-classes) = len(refined-oracles)
  ‚ä® each class ‚àà {"soft", "structural", "deterministic"}

‚ä¢ collect-results
  given refiner-*‚Üírefined-oracles
  given refiner-*‚Üírefined-classes
  given decompose‚Üísub-oracles
  given decompose‚Üíclassifications
  yield sub-oracles'[], classifications'[], soft-count'

  ‚à¥ Merge refined results back into the oracle list:

    1. Keep non-soft oracles from ¬´decompose‚Üísub-oracles¬ª (those
       classified "structural" or "deterministic") ‚Äî already leaves.
    2. For each refiner in the refiner-* cells, replace
       the original soft sub-oracle with its refined-oracles[] and
       refined-classes[].
    3. Output the combined list as sub-oracles'[], classifications'[],
       and soft-count' (count of entries still classified "soft").

  ‚ä® len(sub-oracles') = len(classifications')
  ‚ä® len(sub-oracles') ‚â• len(decompose‚Üísub-oracles)
  ‚ä® soft-count' = count(classifications', c -> c = "soft")
  ‚ä® soft-count' ‚â§ decompose‚Üísoft-count

‚ä¢‚àò refine-loop(decompose, api-artifact‚Üíendpoints, api-artifact‚Üínaming, api-artifact‚Üíerrors, api-artifact‚Üíauth)
  through spawn-sub-decomposers, collect-results
  until collect-results‚Üísoft-count' = 0
  max 3

  -- Each iteration: take soft sub-oracles ‚Üí spawn per-oracle refiners ‚Üí
  -- collect refined replacements. The updated oracle list replaces
  -- decompose's output for the next iteration.
  --
  -- v0.2: api-artifact fields are fixed parameter bindings that persist
  -- across all iterations, providing stable context for decomposition.
  --
  -- Interface frozen: decompose always yields sub-oracles[],
  -- classifications[], soft-count. Only granularity evolves.
  --
  -- Convergence: each iteration replaces soft oracles with more
  -- specific ones, driving soft-count toward 0. Max 3 as safety.

‚ä¢‚ä¢ spawn-crystallizers
  given collect-results‚Üísub-oracles'
  given collect-results‚Üíclassifications'
  given api-artifact‚Üíendpoints
  given api-artifact‚Üínaming
  given api-artifact‚Üíerrors
  given api-artifact‚Üíauth
  given ¬ßcheck-template
  yield ¬ßcheck-cells[]
  until len(check-cells) = len(collect-results‚Üísub-oracles')
  max 20
  replace

  ‚à¥ For each oracle in ¬´collect-results‚Üísub-oracles'¬ª, spawn a
    crystallizer cell from ¬´¬ßcheck-template¬ª that converts the oracle
    text into a concrete deterministic check against the API artifact.

    For "deterministic" oracles: exact value match or containment.
    For "structural" oracles: pattern match or property check.
    Each check must reference a specific field from api-artifact.

  ‚ä® len(check-cells) = len(collect-results‚Üísub-oracles')
  ‚ä® each check-cell targets exactly one oracle

‚ä¢ check-template ‚ñ∏ crystallized
  given oracle-text
  given endpoints
  given naming
  given errors
  given auth
  yield holds, evidence

  ‚ä¢= holds ‚Üê <deterministic check of oracle-text against artifact field>
  ‚ä¢= evidence ‚Üê <the specific artifact value that was checked>

  ‚ä® holds ‚àà {true, false}
  ‚ä® evidence != ""

‚ä¢ assemble-hierarchy
  given root-oracle‚Üítext
  given collect-results‚Üísub-oracles'
  given collect-results‚Üíclassifications'
  given check-*‚Üíholds
  given check-*‚Üíevidence
  yield hierarchy-tree, depth, leaf-count, all-pass

  ‚à¥ Build the oracle hierarchy tree:

    Root: ¬´root-oracle‚Üítext¬ª (level 0, soft)
    ‚îî‚îÄ Level 1+: sub-oracles with their classifications
       ‚îî‚îÄ Leaves: crystallized checks with holds/evidence

    Format as indented text showing each oracle, its classification,
    its crystallized check result (pass/fail), and the evidence used.

    Compute:
    - depth: maximum nesting level in the tree
    - leaf-count: total crystallized leaf checks
    - all-pass: true only if every leaf holds = true

  ‚ä® depth ‚â• 2
  ‚ä® leaf-count = len(collect-results‚Üísub-oracles')
  ‚ä® contains(hierarchy-tree, root-oracle‚Üítext)
  ‚ä® if all-pass then all(check-*‚Üíholds, h -> h = true)

‚ä¢ verify-coverage ‚ñ∏ crystallized
  given assemble-hierarchy‚Üíleaf-count
  given assemble-hierarchy‚Üídepth
  given assemble-hierarchy‚Üíall-pass
  yield valid, verdict

  ‚ä¢= valid ‚Üê (assemble-hierarchy‚Üíleaf-count ‚â• 8 and assemble-hierarchy‚Üídepth ‚â• 2)
  ‚ä¢= verdict ‚Üê if valid and assemble-hierarchy‚Üíall-pass then "oracle chain complete: all leaves pass"
               else if valid and not assemble-hierarchy‚Üíall-pass then "oracle chain complete: some leaves fail"
               else if assemble-hierarchy‚Üíleaf-count < 8 then "insufficient decomposition depth"
               else "hierarchy too shallow"

  ‚ä® verdict ‚àà {"oracle chain complete: all leaves pass", "oracle chain complete: some leaves fail", "insufficient decomposition depth", "hierarchy too shallow"}
  ‚ä® if valid then assemble-hierarchy‚Üíleaf-count ‚â• 8
